author: sun-sentinel.com
title: Heritage-Delray rolls past Newman
text:
AMERICAN HERITAGE-DELRAY 49, CARDINAL NEWMAN 10: The Stallions kept their playoff hopes in line with a District 7-3A victory on Friday night in West Palm Beach.
With an Oxbridge Academy victory over Cardinal Newman in two weeks, Heritage-Delray (5-2, 1-1 in district) would become the district runner-up.
The Stallions advanced tio the Class 3A state championship game last year before losing to Jacksonville Trinity Christian.
